ococcus, it is equal to few hundreds of nm, likely to promote its adhesion\nto the sample. While gliding, the Nostoc secretes a slime layer the thickness\nof which is in the nanometer range and increases with the gliding speed. These\nresults open a large window on new studies of both dynamical phenomena of\npractical and fundamental interests such as the formation of biofilms and\ndynamic properties of bacteria in real physiological conditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Dec 2012 04:24:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 8 Feb 2013 08:43:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2013 07:17:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
